      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BE A COWBOY (3) went straight to the front and never headed when winning by a space two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 4 lengths at this track (19.73). Has claims if he runs up to expectations. BRUREE LUCK (7) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing sixth (19.82) at this track last time. Yet to miss the placings from three starts out of this box. Worth another chance. AUSSIE SAVANNAH (1) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 20.02 beating Irinka Ashley. Should be in this for a long way. SODA TURKEY (6) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a Grade 5 at this track over 350m.",
